The paper discusses a clustering model and proposes a new algorithm for global optimization. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is a hybrid genetic algorithm, which involves optimization techniques such as crossover and mutation, indicating a possible fit for the neural and evolutionary computing sub-category (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of solution quality, which suggests a possible fit for the data mining (cs.DM) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
